# Integrating {{ isa_name }} into QEMU

Generated by ISA-Archive. This directory mirrors the QEMU source tree layout.

## Quick start (automated)

```bash
# Point at your QEMU 9.x source checkout:
bash patch_qemu.sh /path/to/qemu-src

# Then build:
cd /path/to/qemu-src
./configure --target-list={{ isa_name | lower }}-softmmu --disable-docs --disable-werror
ninja -C build qemu-system-{{ isa_name | lower }}
```

## What `patch_qemu.sh` does

1. **Copies** `target/{{ isa_name | lower }}/`, `hw/{{ isa_name | lower }}/`, and `configs/` into the QEMU tree.
2. **Appends** four one-line entries to existing QEMU source files (idempotent):
   - `target/Kconfig` ‚Äî `source {{ isa_name | lower }}/Kconfig`
   - `target/meson.build` ‚Äî `subdir('{{ isa_name | lower }}')`
   - `hw/Kconfig` ‚Äî `source {{ isa_name | lower }}/Kconfig`
   - `hw/meson.build` ‚Äî `subdir('{{ isa_name | lower }}')`
3. **Adds** `QEMU_ARCH_{{ isa_name | upper | replace("-", "_") }}` to `include/sysemu/arch_init.h`.

## Manual steps (if you prefer)

```bash
QEMU=/path/to/qemu-src
ISA={{ isa_name | lower }}

# Copy files
cp -r target/$ISA/  $QEMU/target/$ISA/
cp -r hw/$ISA/      $QEMU/hw/$ISA/
cp -r configs/      $QEMU/configs/

# Patch source files
echo "source $ISA/Kconfig"  >> $QEMU/target/Kconfig
echo "subdir('$ISA')"       >> $QEMU/target/meson.build
echo "source $ISA/Kconfig"  >> $QEMU/hw/Kconfig
echo "subdir('$ISA')"       >> $QEMU/hw/meson.build

# Add to arch_init.h enum (replace N with the next available bit number):
# QEMU_ARCH_{{ isa_name | upper | replace("-", "_") }} = (1 << N),
```

